03/05/2004
BUCHAREST, Romania -- At a rally Saturday (1 May), Prime Minister Adrian Nastase vowed that salaries and pensions would climb in the next four years with the implementation of the government's labour strategy. He said salaries would double in that time, while the average pension would increase by 50 per cent. Nastase added that the government is also considering subsidies for university students and modernising the health system. (Mediafax - 01/05/04)
